description:
As it currently stands, both the USNS Comfort & Mercy are NOT taking any COVID-19 patients, until their mission is changed. All COVID-19 testing is done (and cleared) at the hospital before the patient boards the ship. The current patients aboard each ship runs the 'gamut' of what you would see in a community hospital. What was listed was gun shot wounds, broken legs, traumatic accidents, gastrointestinal issues, as well as heart & lung problems.
